    <item>
      <title>Strange shift key behaviour when renaming files in ubuntu</title>
      <link>https://yantonov.com/post/2016-05-10-strange-shift-key-behaviour-when-renaming-files-in-ubuntu/</link>
      <guid>https://yantonov.com/post/2016-05-10-strange-shift-key-behaviour-when-renaming-files-in-ubuntu/</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 10 May 2016 08:45:32 +0500</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;There is a really puzzling behaviour in Nautilus regarding my Shift key. Consider the following scenario:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose any file to rename&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;During renaming i can type just fine unless i need a capital letter. If i type a capital letter (using shift) then focus shifts to some file at the same folder.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clarification: Current shortcut to change layout LShift+RShift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Solution:
Change shortcut to, for example, LCtrl + LShift (System Settings -&amp;gt; Text Entry)and the problem disappears.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
